parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Leaks and Fuel Pump Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel tank leaks and fuel pump failure can cause gas vapors to fill the garage, leading to a fire or explosion hazard. This issue can also cause fuel to leak onto the exhaust pipes, creating a risk of fire or explosion while driving.
symptoms: Strong fuel smell inside the car

especially when the fuel tank is filled to half or more; fuel leaks from the driver's side fuel tank; fuel smell in the cabin of the vehicle; gas smell coming from the fender area; loud gas smell when filling up the fuel tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission shifter getting stuck in park can cause the vehicle to be unable to move, leading to potential safety risks, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: The transmission shifter becomes stuck in park
even with the brake pedal depressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch pedal can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel leak and smell can cause a fire hazard, leading to potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle emits a strong fuel smell
even when the tank is not full.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Valve Guide Wear and Valve Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the valve guides and valves can cause the engine to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and fires.
The failure of the harmonic balancer can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of control and accidents.
The failure of the needle bearings can cause the engine to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and fires.
